title.narrative: Jordan Loan Guarantee Facility Ceiling Increase

description.narrative: (Jordan): The Jordan Loan Guarantee Facility (JLGF) improves access to finance for micro, small and medium enterprises (MSMEs) in Jordan. The activity provides partial loan guarantees from the Overseas Private Investment Corporation OPIC to support credit-worthy but previously underserved MSMEs. JLGF is a nationwide activity and has no sector restrictions, and guarantees cover 75 percent of the loan principal for businesses regardless of their location or the gender of the business owner. JLGF provides technical assistance to its partner banks to help them institutionalize international best practices in MSME credit, including incorporating cash flow analysis in lending decisions and reducing the reliance on collateral as the sole criterion for credit approval. Furthermore, JLGF provides technical assistance to the MSMEs to become bankable through tailored training on financial planning and projections for businesses.
